{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d7e98263-248b-4011-bbb7-81757292d3bf","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Filter syntax** — MTP doesn't use VSTest's `--filter`. Instead, use the `--filter` flag with MTP's own syntax. The `&` operator and `~` (contains) work differently:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xunit v2):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xunit v3):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **Traits** must use `trait=Name=Value` (not just `Name=Value`).\n- `~` (contains) and `&` (and) still work in MTP, so that part stays the same.\n\n**2. Trait attribute** — xUnit v3 replaced `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` with a dedicated `[Category(\"Smoke\")]` attribute (though `[Trait]` still works for now). No change is strictly required here, but if you adopt the new attribute the trait key stays `Category`.\n\nSo your CI command becomes:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0d4acac4-f9f9-4245-a27e-49cd5a7088c5","outputTokens":316},"id":"0f42aa17-45a2-4a09-98bb-dc1793000291","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:55:59.956Z","parentId":"15f8a8c0-3105-40f3-870c-9a3580363636"}
